Package com.cafean.CodePlugins

Class MEFeaturePlugin

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.CodePlugins.MEPlugin
      • com.cafean.CodePlugins.MEFeaturePlugin
  • public abstract class MEFeaturePlugin
extends MEPlugin
    This is used to implement a new feature plugin for the model editor. It contains all of the functions common between feature plugins in the model editor.

      • load

        public abstract void load​(AbstractModel loadedModel,
                          PibFile pibfile)
        This is called on all Feature plugins when a model has been loaeded. This allows feature plugins that need to load local data associated with that model to read that data from the end of the file.
        Parameters:
        loadedModel - the AbstractModel that has just been loaded from disk.
        pibfile - the local file that is being read in.

      • save

        public abstract void save​(AbstractModel savedModel,
                          PibFile pibfile)
        This is called on all Feature plugins when a model has been stored. This allows feature plugins that need to store local data associated with that model to append the data to the end of the file.
        Parameters:
        savedModel - the AbstractModel that has just been saved to disk.
        pibfile - the local file that is being written out.

      • modelAdded

        public abstract void modelAdded​(AbstractModel model)
        This is called on all Feature plugins when a new model has been added to the model editor. This allows all plugins that need to store local data associated with that type of model to initalizes any data they need.
        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel just added to the model Editor.

      • modelSaved

        public void modelSaved​(AbstractModel model)
        This is called on all Feature plugins when a model has been saved in model editor. This allows all plugins that need to update to change after the model has been saved.
        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractModel just added to the model Editor.
